{{Infobox book | name = Dril Official "Mr. Ten Years" Anniversary Collection | image = Dril Official "Mr. Ten Years" Anniversary Collection.jpg | border = yes | alt = A blurry, blue-tinted image of Jack Nicholson with the word "DRIL" in all caps | author = [[dril]] | illustrator = dril | publisher = Self-published | pub_date = {{start date|2018|08|21}} | pages = 420 | isbn = 978-1724941688 | website = }}
'''''Dril Official "Mr. Ten Years" Anniversary Collection''''' is the first book by [[dril]], a pseudonymous [[Twitter]] user known for his [[Surreal humour|absurdist humor]]. The book is the author's compilation of the account's best tweets from its first ten years, alongside new original illustrations. The tweets are sorted into sections by topic. The book was [[Self-publishing|self-published]] in [[paperback]] and [[E-book|ebook]] formats. According to the preface, dril published the book in print so that his tweets would survive a future [[societal collapse]] and [[digital dark age]].
The book received generally positive reviews, with praise directed at dril's distinctive humor and creativity. Although the book's written material was already available online for free, critics generally agreed that the compilation's quality and dril's influence justified its publication.
== Development and publication == {{Main|dril}}
The @dril Twitter account began posting in September 2008; in the years that followed, dril became well-known for his idiosyncratic humor and accrued a [[cult following]]. In January 2017, dril opened a [[Patreon]] account for fans to make monthly payments in support of his tweets and future projects, including "video, illustration, and long-form writing."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://news.avclub.com/get-involved-internet-donate-to-twitter-god-dril-s-p-1798256658 |title=Get Involved, Internet!: Donate to Twitter god dril's Patreon so he can 'create Hell' |last=Colburn |first=Randall |date=January 20, 2017 |website=[[The A.V. Club]] |accessdate=August 24, 2017 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170826031518/http://news.avclub.com/get-involved-internet-donate-to-twitter-god-dril-s-p-1798256658 |archive-date=August 26, 2017 |dead-url=no}}</ref> On the Patreon, dril described his plans for two book projects:
{{quote|as I believe I've mentioned earlier, I am working on two (2) new books, and as of right now your generous contributions are mainly funding the completion of these projects: [...] BOOK #1: Just absolutely, cover to cover, the worst bullshit imaginable [...] all loosely tied together with a narrative adjacent to the 'Mythos' surrounding my posts. [...] BOOK #2: a lot of people ask me for a 'Best of' release, like some kind of coffee table book of my top posts, and while I think a book containing nothing but short messages you can easily dig up online would be sort of Shitty, I decided to make it worthwhile by filling the thing up with new stuff as well.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.patreon.com/posts/what-is-this-why-8190514 |title=<nowiki>'</nowiki>what is this shit. why am i giving you money<nowiki>'</nowiki> |last=dril |date=February 21, 2017 |website=''[[Patreon]]'' |accessdate=August 24, 2017 |url-access=subscription}} {{subscription required}}</ref>}}
dril [[Self-publishing|self-published]] the compilation project as ''Dril Official "Mr. Ten Years" Anniversary Collection'' in August 2018.<ref name="dril book">{{cite web |url = https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/mb4dvb/dril-official-mr-ten-years-anniversary-collection-book-vgtrn |title = Dril, the Only Account on Twitter, Has a Book Now |last = Slattery |first = Peter |date = August 23, 2018 |website = [[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] |publisher = [[Vice Media]] |accessdate = August 23, 2018 |archiveurl = https://archive.today/20180823191614/https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/mb4dvb/dril-official-mr-ten-years-anniversary-collection-book-vgtrn |archivedate = August 23, 2018 |dead-url = no}}</ref> It was released in [[paperback]] and [[e-book|ebook]] formats. It was initially made available to download for [[Amazon Kindle]], but was subsequently withdrawn from that format.<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.dailydot.com/unclick/dril-twitter-book/ |title = Dril, everyone's favorite Twitter weirdo, has a book out now |last = Ritzen |first = Stacey |date = August 23, 2018 |website = [[The Daily Dot]] |accessdate = November 11, 2018 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180824114612/https://www.dailydot.com/unclick/dril-twitter-book/ |archivedate = August 24, 2018 |dead-url = no}}</ref> On his Patreon, dril explained that the Kindle version was withdrawn because it was "displaying incorrectly".<ref>{{cite web |url = https://www.patreon.com/posts/book-pdf-version-20970439 |title = Book: PDF Version |last = dril |date = August 24, 2018 |website = ''[[Patreon]]'' |accessdate = November 11, 2018 |url-access = subscription}} {{subscription required}}</ref> Afterward, the book became available as a [[PDF]].<ref>{{Cite tweet |user=dril |number=1033163882766852099 |date = August 24, 2018 |title=you may now buy the pdf Version of the book for $8 [...] i will shut the fuck up now. thank you |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181012022707/https://twitter.com/dril/status/1033163882766852099 |archive-date=October 12, 2018 |dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="highsnobiety">{{cite web |url = https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/dril-twitter-anniversary-book/ |title = Twitter Legend Dril Is Releasing a Book |last = Nembhard |first = Candice |date = August 28, 2018 |website = [[Highsnobiety]] |accessdate = November 11, 2018 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20180828170843/https://www.highsnobiety.com/p/dril-twitter-anniversary-book/ |archivedate = August 28, 2018 |dead-url = no}}</ref>
== Content == The [[420 (cannabis culture)|420]]-page book compiles 1,500 of the account's best posts from its first ten years, as selected by the author.<ref name="dril book" /> The compiled tweets are sorted into topic areas by chapter, which are presented alphabetically.<ref name="Stephen" /> Individual tweets do not include the date they were originally published.<ref name="Stephen" /> The book features 70 new illustrations by dril.<ref name="dril book" /> According to dril's preface, he published the book to preserve his posts in the event of a [[societal collapse]] that takes Twitter's servers offline.<ref name="Stephen" /><ref name="preface">{{cite book |author=[[dril]] |year=2018 |title=Dril Official "Mr. Ten Years" Anniversary Collection |chapter=Preface |publisher=Self-published with [[CreateSpace]] |isbn=978-1724941688}}</ref> dril predicts a "miserable, Offline Hell" of the future in which his posts have been "Permanently Decommissioned", alluding to [[FEMA camps conspiracy theory|FEMA conspiracies]] and "[[Jade Helm 15 conspiracy theories|Jade Helm 15 bull shit]]".<ref name="preface" /> dril says the book is a means to preserve his content in the aftermath of a civilization collapse and [[digital dark age]]:
{{quote|This book is, without a doubt, the [[Svalbard Global Seed Vault]], of posts, designed to withstand the fall of civilization and ensure that my invaluable Content permeates the hearts and minds of post-collapse generations, in order to prevent the whole of humanity from reverting to the way of the cave man.<ref name="preface" />}}
The book is sorted into 72 sections, sorted alphabetically by topic or theme:<ref name="Stephen" />
{{columns-list|colwidth=10em| * Animals * [[Buttocks|Ass]] * [[Barbecue|BBQ]] * Beauty & Fashion * [[Beer]] * Birds * Brands * Cars * Charity & Activism * Crime & Punishment * Death * [[Deep state|Deep State]] * Diaper * [[Human penis|Dick]] * [[Digimon]]Otis * Dining * Disease & Medicine * Dogs * Drugs & Smoking * Dumb Asses * Economy & The Markets * Fast Food * Fatherhood * Gaming * Gender * Girls * God & Religion * Grab Bag * Ground Hog * Guns * [[Halloween]] * ''[[Halo (franchise)|Halo]]'' * Holidays * Hollywood * [[James Bond]] * Jeans * Life Hacks * Luxury * Mayor * Military * Money * Muscle & Fitness * Music * News * [[September 11 attacks|Nine Eleven]] * Nostalgia * Nudity * [[Barack Obama|Obama]] * [[Online and offline|Online]] * [[Parkour]] * Pigs * [[Urine|Piss]] * Police * Politics * Racism * Rants * Rats * Sex * [[Shit]] * Sorrow * Sports * Tech * Teens * Television * The Boys * Toilet * Tough Guys * [[Internet troll|Trolls]] * Twitter * Wife * Wisdom * [[YouTube|You Tube]] {{sic}}<ref>{{cite book |author=[[dril]] |year=2018 |title=Dril Official "Mr. Ten Years" Anniversary Collection |chapter=Table of Contents |publisher=Self-published with [[CreateSpace]] |isbn=978-1724941688}}</ref> }}
== Reception == In an article for ''Vice'', Peter Slattery wrote "[o]rdinarily, throwing together a book full of old tweets would seem pretty lazy, but given how much legit influence dril has had on Twitter humor and online culture at large, everybody probably owes the account at least 20 bucks."<ref name="dril book" /> Reviewing the book for ''Vice'', Rachel Pick concluded that the book was worth it "so that one day, centuries from now, after the bombs go off and [[Electromagnetic pulse|EMPs]] take out the electrical grid, long after Twitter has died, a solitary wanderer may find a scrap of paper buried in the ruins of my Brooklyn apartment building, and they will lift it up to the dying sun and squint through their protective goggles to read" a dril tweet.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/qvmqew/dril-new-book-tweets-interview | last = Pick | first = Rachel | title = Cowards and Trolls Log Off: Dril's New Book Is Awesome | website = [[Vice (magazine)|Vice]] | publisher = [[Vice Media]] | date = August 28, 2018 | accessdate = September 4, 2018 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20180904191243/https://motherboard.vice.com/en_us/article/qvmqew/dril-new-book-tweets-interview | archive-date = September 4, 2018 | deadurl = no}}</ref> Bijan Stephen at ''The Verge'' said that, "[d]espite literally being a book of tweets, ''Mr. Ten Years'' chronicles Dril's rise from a funny writer to a writer who's defined the way people write and think about internet culture."<ref name="Stephen">{{cite web |url=https://www.theverge.com/2018/9/27/17907568/dril-book-official-mr-ten-years-anniversary-collection-review-tweets-twitter |title=@Dril Is the Best Chronicler of the Internet's Last Decade |last=Stephen |first=Bijan |date=September 27, 2018 |website=[[The Verge]] |accessdate=October 8, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180927225603/https://www.theverge.com/2018/9/27/17907568/dril-book-official-mr-ten-years-anniversary-collection-review-tweets-twitter |archive-date=September 27, 2018 |dead-url=no}}</ref>
Writing for ''[[HuffPost]]'', Sean T. Collins called the book "simply too funny for me to read for more than a page or two at a time without laughing so hard, I feel physically ill."<ref name="Collins">{{cite web |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/dril-and-the-boys-twitter_us_5bb66529e4b028e1fe3bfd71 |last=Collins |first=Sean T. |date=October 5, 2018 |title=The Love Song of Dril and the Boys |website=[[HuffPost]] |accessdate=October 7, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181005205522/https://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/dril-and-the-boys-twitter_us_5bb66529e4b028e1fe3bfd71 |archive-date=October 5, 2018 |dead-url=no}}</ref> At ''[[Geek.com]]'', Jordan Minor called the book a "glorious exception" to the expectation that online jokes taken offline can only result in "cursed", mediocre "nightmares like [[Shit My Dad Says]]: [[$h*! My Dad Says|The TV Show]]".<ref name="Minor">{{cite web |url=https://www.geek.com/shop/geek-pick-dril-official-mr-ten-years-anniversary-collection-1751232/ |last=Minor |first=Jordan |date=September 4, 2018 |title=Geek Pick: ''Dril Official 'Mr. Ten Years' Anniversary Collection'' |website=[[Geek.com]] |accessdate=November 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111224039/https://www.geek.com/shop/geek-pick-dril-official-mr-ten-years-anniversary-collection-1751232/ |archive-date=November 11, 2018 |dead-url=no}}</ref> Minor praised dril's illustrations, which he said "flesh out the look of the character beyond his [[Jack Nicholson]] roots" and show "there are a bunch of ways to depict a gross old parody internet man in sunglasses."<ref name="Minor" /> In an essay for the online men's [[lifestyle magazine]] ''Mel Magazine'', Miles Klee praised the book's section on "Tough Guys".<ref name="Klee">{{cite web |url=https://melmagazine.com/en-us/story/how-dril-foretold-the-collapse-of-man |last=Klee |first=Miles |date=October 10, 2018 |title=How Dril Foretold the Collapse of Man |website=Mel Magazine |publisher=[[Dollar Shave Club]] |accessdate=November 11, 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181111232625/https://melmagazine.com/en-us/story/how-dril-foretold-the-collapse-of-man |archive-date=November 11, 2018 |dead-url=no}}</ref> According to Klee, the tweets in that section "beautifully [[Deconstruction|deconstructed]]" some men's "commitment to archaic notions of dudely stoicism" and demonstrated "the character's inability to confess weakness, shame or error."<ref name="Klee" />
