{{italic title}} '''''Farhang-e-rabbani (jadid)''''' is an [[Urdu]]-[[Bengali language|Bangla]]بنگلااُردُو dictionary. It came to light in 1952. It was certified by Dr. [[Muhammad Shahidullah]] and [[Suniti Kumar Chatterji]]. It was the first Bangla-Urdu dictionary, when [[Bangladesh]] was part of the [[Dominion of Pakistan]] as [[East Bengal]]. This dictionary was collected or made by [[Shiraj Rabbani]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Prometheus-Academic Collections|url=http://hdl.handle.net/10108/39250}} Title : Farhang-e-Rabbani : Urdu-Bengali dictionary / [Sirāja Rabbānī] ; bhūmikā, Sunītikumāra Caṭṭopādhyāẏa Authors : Rabbānī, Sirāja Chatterji, Suniti Kumar, 1890–1977 Publisher : Rabbani Publications Issue Date : [1952] Pages : 21, 671 p. Size : 18&nbsp;cm Title Language Code : Urdu Text Language Code : Urdu, Bengali Book ID : 586872 </ref>
