'''Jodi Hauptman''' is a Senior [[Curator]] at The [[Museum of Modern Art]], New York.<ref name=MoMA>{{cite web|url=http://press.moma.org/2014/04/jodi-hauptman-senior-curator/|title=Jodi Hauptman, Senior Curator|publisher=Museum of Modern Art|accessdate=23 December 2015}}</ref> She has organized landmark exhibitions such as "Henri Matisse: The Cut-Outs" and "Georges Seurat - The Drawings". She most recently organized the critically acclaimed Degas: A Strange New Beauty also at the Museum of Modern Art, New York which the NEw York Times called "a large but thrillingly intimate exhibition." She appeared on Charlie Rose to discuss both the Matisse and Degas shows, respectively.<ref>https://charlierose.com/videos/28063</ref><ref>https://charlierose.com/videos/4528</ref><ref>http://press.moma.org/2015/07/edgar-degas/</ref><ref>https://www.nytimes.com/2016/03/25/arts/design/the-moderndegas-you-havent-seen.html</ref><ref name=MoMA/>

