{{Italic title}} '''''Manual of the Higher Plants of Oregon''''' was an early flora of plants of Oregon written by [[Morton Peck]].<ref name=OEMP>Morton Peck, Oregon Encyclopedia, [http://www.oregonencyclopedia.org/articles/peck_morton_1871_1959_/#.VCiLSizn_IU]</ref>
It was praised for its format, portabliity, [[phylogenetic key]]s, having new species recorded, and completeness of both descriptions of plants and [[florstic province|physiographic provinces]].<ref name=OEMP>Morton Peck, Oregon Encyclopedia, [http://www.oregonencyclopedia.org/articles/peck_morton_1871_1959_/#.VCiLSizn_IU]</ref> The second edition (1961) includes many changes to the first edition (1941), which according to Peck, "is now decidedly out of date."<ref>{{cite book|last1=Peck|first1=Morton|title=A Manual Of The Higher Plants Of Oregon|date=1961|publisher=[[Binfords & Mort]]|location=[[Hillsboro, Oregon|Hillsboro]]|page=4|edition=Second}}</ref>
